scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120). This needs to be tested against the previous results.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774371037357}}
{"type":"message","id":"60c9efaf","parentId":"38ba996f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:50:37.363Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x6qabopvyjug_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 124915\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's been significant work on CFI compression synthesis\r\n3. The pending items include:\r\n   - Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n   - Distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n   - Implement CFI filtering\r\n   - Wire Breakaway to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n   - Design actual compression network\r\n\r\nThe key insight from this session is:\r\n- **Three-dimensional compression filter**: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n- **Compression objective**: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThe most impactful next step seems to be implementing the hybrid scoring experiment (Strategy C) that was identified as the next experiment. This directly follows from the CFI compression synthesis work.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist and what I can do:\r\n- `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` - the synthesis document\r\n- `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md` - gap-decay synthesis\r\n- `pulse.ps1` - the pulse script\r\n\r\nI should create an experiment plan or implement the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring. Let me create a concrete experiment script that implements Strategy C: the hybrid scoring approach.\r\n\r\nThe formula identified is:\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThis handles:\r\n- Constant format (freq=160, CFI=1): score = 1 × min(1, 160/120) = 1 × 1 = 1 (BUT we need to cap at freq < 120)\r\n- Research trajectory (freq=60, CFI=0.7): score = 0.7 × min(1, 60/120) = 0.7 × 0.5 = 0.35\r\n\r\n\r\n- Ideal (freq=80, CFI=0.8): score = 0.8 × min(1, 80/120) = 0.8 × 0.67 = 0.536\r\n\r\nI realize the current formula still allows constant format tokens to score highly. The three-dimensional filter CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120) needs a more nuanced approach to truly distinguish meaningful research tokens from constant format artifacts.\r\n\r\nThe proposed refinement score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) × decay(freq) provides a more sophisticated scoring mechanism. By incorporating a decay function for frequency, we can more effectively differentiate between different token types and capture the subtle variations in research trajectory tokens.\r\n\r\nI'll design a comprehensive experiment script that implements these refined filtering strategies, carefully mapping out how each scoring approach captures the desired token characteristics.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression synthesis identified Strategy C (hybrid CFI×Freq scoring) as the next experiment, but no implementation exists yet. The key insight is that constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1) must be distinguished from research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the hybrid scoring experiment script that implements Strategy C - the three-dimensional filter with combined CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring to validate the compression hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI×Freq Hybrid Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\n# Created: 2026-03-24\r\n# Following: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md findings\r\n\r\n# HYPOTHESIS\r\n# Combined scoring: score(T) = CFI(T) × sqrt(freq(T)/120)\r\n# This penalizes constant-format tokens (freq=160, score=1.15 → capped at 1.0)\r\n# While preserving research tokens (freq=60, CFI=0.7 → score=0.35)\r\n# AND applying 3D filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n\r\n# CONSTANT FORMAT TOKENS (to exclude):\r\n# - \"for next instantiation\" (freq=160, CFI=1.00)\r\n# - \"pulse\" (freq=160+, CFI=1.00)  \r\n# - \"completed at:\" (freq=160, CFI=1.00)\r\n# - \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96) ← borderline, needs freq filter\r\n\r\n# EXPERIMENT PARAMETERS\r\n$TotalPulses = 200\r\n$TrainSplit = 0.8  # 160 train, 40 test\r\n$TestSplit = 0.2\r\n\r\n# SCORING FUNCTIONS\r\n# Strategy A: freq-only (baseline)\r\nfunction Get-FreqScore($freq) { return $freq / 160.0 }\r\n\r\n# Strategy B: CFI-only (from prior experiment)\r\nfunction Get-CFIScore($cfi) { return $cfi }\r\n\r\n# Strategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 (THIS EXPERIMENT)\r\nfunction Get-HybridScore($cfi, $freq) { \r\n    $freqNorm = [Math]::Min(1.0, $freq / 120.0)\r\n    return $cfi * [Math]::Sqrt($freqNorm)\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Strategy C+3D: Hybrid + 3D filter\r\nfunction Get-3DFilterScore($cfi, $freq) {\r\n    if ($cfi -ge 0.5 -and $freq -ge 3 -and $freq -lt 120) {\r\n        return Get-HybridScore $cfi $freq\r\n    }\r\n    return 0.0\r\n}\r\n\r\n# THREE-D\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:49:40\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774371037360}}
