{"type":"message","id":"0396e35a","parentId":"3f52cefe","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:50:48.339Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. Let me summarize the pulse results.","thinkingSignature":"5c0a08eff50494384a2fa1b7a487d8a50895717df833e33d2de435da2b0253ac"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 12:50 PM ET**\n\n**✅ Completed:**\n- Proposed a new experiment file: `research/HYBRID_SCORING_EXPERIMENT.md` implementing Strategy C (hybrid CFI×Freq scoring with 3D filter)\n- Previous mutation `2026-03-24 124915.mutation` was **rejected** (threshold-only approach — susceptible to the constant format problem)\n- Committed pulse checkpoint: `01565a0`\n\n**🔍 Key Insight from CFI Analysis:**\nPure threshold filtering fails because constant-format metaprogramming tokens (e.g., \"for next instantiation\", \"pulse\", \"completed at:\") score CFI=1.0 at freq≈160 — they *look* like high-information tokens but carry zero actual information.\n\n**📋 Proposed Experiment — Strategy C:**\n- **Formula:** `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)`\n- **3D Filter:** `CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)` — excludes constant format (freq≥120) and noise (freq<3)\n- **Goal:** Distinguish true research trajectory tokens from high-frequency metaprogramming artifacts\n\n**Status:** 1 mutation pending (awaiting review/apply)"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2084,"output":294,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14515,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774371040894}}
